BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Eco Petals: Crafting a Recycled Bouquet — Sebastopol Center For 
 the Arts\, California
DTSTART:20260402T000000
DTEND:20260403T000000
UID:dff78e5cffddf966751a7a12c5653fd6@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Eco Petals: Crafting a Recycled Bouquet\n\n  \n    \n      \n 
        \n          $70.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\nThursday\, April 
 2\, 2026\; 6PM-9PM$60 + $10 Materials feeCreate a whimsical upcycled bouqu
 et using imagination and an assortment of found and recycled papers. In th
 is playful workshop\, you’ll learn simple techniques for shaping paper f
 lowers and combining colors\, textures\, and unexpected materials. No expe
 rience needed—just come ready to explore and leave with a one-of-a-kind 
 handmade bouquet. All supplies provided.About the Instructor: Rendell Hour
 igan received a BBA in Marketing from Texas Tech University\, and has purs
 ued art for over 25 years\, focusing on sustainable mixed media. She has s
 tudied with artists including Chery Baird\, Jenny London\, and Teri Sloat\
 , exploring drawing\, collage\, and soft pastels. Her training includes wo
 rkshops and courses in art journaling\, mosaics\, and mark-making. She’s
  exhibited work at the Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, The Graton Gallery
 \, and her SOFA district studio. Drawn to the beauty of discarded material
 s and passionate about recycling\, she incorporates reclaimed materials in
 to her work and now leads art workshops to inspire eco-conscious creativit
 y in others.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n
 \n\n          \n            \n              \n                Add to cart
