SUMMARY:Paper Lanterns Workshop — Sebastopol Center For the Arts\, Calif
 ornia
DTSTART:20260419T000000
DTEND:20260420T000000
UID:0b2ea899ef80f7885f9155ba075c8bb1@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Paper Lanterns Workshop\n\n  \n    \n      \n        \n       
    $70.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\nSunday\, April 19\, 2026\; 1:00PM
  – 4:00PM$60 + $10 Materials feeDiscover the magic of paper cutting In t
 his one-day workshop making your own paper lantern.  Participants will le
 arn paper cutting design and knife technique\, and create a unique\, illum
 inated piece of art. After exploring examples of paper cutting artists an
 d their work\, students will dream up their own paper lantern designs to e
 xecute with guidance and instruction. Learn how to translate your ideas in
 to a cut paper composition\, then how to cut out your composition with min
 imized frustration. Finally\, we will assemble our lanterns and illuminate
  them to bask in the glow of your efforts. This class will cover: proper 
 knife handling\, foundational paper cutting skills\, and the basics of pap
 er cutting design. A light box will be available if students would like to
  bring reference images to trace onto their lantern materials. This class
  is suitable for artists of all skill levels. All materials included\, inc
 luding an electric votive to illuminate your paper lantern safely. Safety 
 Note: Participants must have strong enough fine motor abilities to handle 
 a sharp blade safely. About the Instructor: Hannah Day received her BA in
  Visual Arts with an emphasis on drawing and printmaking from University o
 f San Diego\, then attended University of Hawaii at Manoa to receive her M
 FA in printmaking. Hannah’s etchings have been internationally shown and
  collected\, but her personal practice also includes paper cutting\, graph
 ite\, watercolor\, mixed media\, and murals. She has taught all ages and m
 any formats (kids\, teens\, adults\, college\, private lessons\, camps\, e
 tc) and many mediums. These days\, Hannah has primarily been teaching wate
 rcolor classes\, but also teaches drawing\, paper cutting\, and pop-up art
 . You can view her work at www.hannahdrawstrees.com\n\n\n\n\n\n          \
 n            \n              \n                Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/paper-lanterns-workshop
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
