BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jizo Peace Project: Clay Gathering — Sebastopol Center For the A
 rts\, California
DTSTART:20260501T000000
DTEND:20260502T000000
UID:e92065ef1ec7da1c4870cde7bb39ca96@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Jizo Peace Project: Clay Gathering for Remembrance and Peace\,
  May\n\n  \n    \n      \n        \n          $10.00\n        \n      \n  
   \n  \n\nFriday\, May 1\, 2026\; 1:30 – 4:00pmDue to limited capacity\,
  we are asking for a suggested donation of $10 to confirm your attendance.
  Bring a copy of your receipt at check-in to Painting/Drawing Studio adjac
 ent to Ceramics StudioJoin us for a monthly\, heart-centered gathering whe
 re we come together to create Jizo guardians out of clay—symbols of comp
 assion\, protection\, and peace. Rooted in the Buddhist tradition and echo
 ed across many cultures\, Jizo figures traditionally honor children and al
 l who have passed\, those in transition\, and those in distress.This ongoi
 ng project is dedicated to remembering those lost to war\, with a special 
 focus now on the approximately 19\,000 children who have perished in Israe
 l and Gaza in recent years. Through the simple\, meditative act of working
  with clay\, we create benevolent beings that will become part of public e
 xhibits and peace sites\, offering spaces for reflection\, mourning\, and 
 hope. Our gatherings conclude with a gentle ritual to honor the lives of t
 hese children.Located in the Painting & Drawing Room. The gathering is ope
 n to ages 12 - adult\, and no prior clay experience is necessary—all cla
 y and basic materials are supplied. Registration is required to participat
 e.Donations are welcome to help cover materials and expenses. More than a 
 class\, this is a shared space of warmth and care—an opportunity to tend
  to our own hearts while taking part in love in action.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\
 n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n          \n            \n 
              \n                Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/jizo-peace-project-clay-gathe
 ring-may
