END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pt. 3: Finding One’s Voice Through Art – A Second Life in Cera
 mics with Ping Zhong — Sebastopol Center For the Arts\, California
DTSTART:20260502T000000
DTEND:20260503T000000
UID:81832a52f7f272fc5bd0f2c33221974a@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Pt. 3: Finding One’s Voice Through Art – A Second Life in 
 Ceramics with Ping Zhong\n\n  \n    \n      \n        \n          $10.00\n
         \n      \n    \n  \n\nSaturday\, May 2\, 2026\; 10am-11amLocated i
 n the Fireside RoomSebArts’ Ceramics Residency Artist\, Ping Zhong\, wil
 l share their personal journey of discovering artistic expression through 
 ceramics later in life\, introducing their work and experiences to illustr
 ate how art can become a meaningful path of self-discovery.Due to limited 
 capacity of the Ceramics Studio\, we are asking for a suggested donation o
 f $10 to confirm your attendance. About the Artist: Ping Zhong’s artisti
 c practice is a continuous exploration of regeneration—of materials\, fo
 rms\, and cultural narratives. She investigates the dialogue between ancie
 nt Chinese pottery and contemporary visual language\, using wheel-throwing
 \, hand-building\, and sculpture to create works in which history and pers
 onal growth converge. This reinterpretation of classical forms is not only
  an artistic method\, but also a philosophical inquiry into the harmony be
 tween past and future. Deeply motivated to uncover the potential within cl
 ay\, Ping pushes the boundaries of design and technique. Her work reflects
  on universal themes: the individual’s place within the community\, the 
 relationship between essence and appearance\, and the evolving connection 
 between nature and society. Through these explorations\, she seeks to crea
 te art that resonates across cultures.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n
 \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n          \n            \n              \n  
               Add to cart
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts\, 282 S High St\, Sebastopol\, CA 
 95472
URL:https://www.sebarts.org/classes-lectures/pt-3-finding-ones-voice-throu
 gh-art-a-second-life-in-ceramics-with-ping-zhong
X-SOURCE:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
END:VEVENT
