SUMMARY:Explore Gel Plate Printing — Sebastopol Center For the Arts\, Ca
 lifornia
DTSTART:20260502T000000
DTEND:20260503T000000
UID:640f56ac648ef534e104d99f8e73bd99@sebarts.org
DESCRIPTION:Explore Gel Plate Printing\, 5/2\n\n  \n    \n      \n        
 \n          $130.00\n        \n      \n    \n  \n\nSaturday\, May 2\, 2026
 \; 11 AM – 3 PMFee: $115 + $15 materials feeAge: 16+ Participants: min. 
 8Learn to create beautiful designs on paper by printing with a gel plate a
 nd acrylic paint. Mixed media artist Catherine Cruz will teach you the bas
 ic skills for using this fun tool from printing textural backgrounds\, to 
 layering colors\, and using stencils and other applications. You will take
  home many prints that can be used for designing collage\, mixed media art
  or greeting cards. This class is suitable for anyone wanting to learn thi
 s unique mono printing style and perfect for beginners.What you’ll get f
 rom this workshop: Methods for applying paint and pulling successful print
 s (Note: Magazine image transfer is not included in this class.)\, Techniq
 ues for creating intricate layered designs\, Creative use of mark-making t
 ools and masks\, Strategies for combining techniques.A variety of papers w
 ill be provided but you are highly encouraged to bring your own papers to 
 experiment on.IMPORTANT: Instructions for where to purchase your materials
  and how to prepare them is provided in the attached PDF. The instructor w
 ill start the class with a demonstration so please arrive a few minutes ea
 rly to get set up so we can start on time.  We will take a short break for
  lunch between 12:30 and 1:00 pm so bring your lunch and a beverage.  Abou
 t the instructor: Catherine Cruz is a French-American artist whose work is
  informed by textures and patterns created by the passing of time and the 
 effects of the natural elements on the built environment.  She holds a Bac
 helor of Science in interior design and she worked in the field of archite
 ctural design and green building certification for over 25 years.  She has
  taught collage and mixed media workshops in the Bay Area and in France si
 nce 2019\, and this is her fifth year at the Sebastopol Center for the Art
 s.  Her studio is located in Sebastopol and she participates in Art Trails
  Open Studios.  You may contact Catherine at beyouartstudio@gmail.com.  Ch
 eck out Catherine’s other classes here:  https://wwws.sebarts.org/visual
 -arts-classes.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n
